Description.LocalizedString: An old, disheveled room that reeks of despair.
A squalid home, but far better than the rest of The Entity's Realm.
A reprieve from the nearby horrors.
Warm and peaceful, the only danger being the tedium of isolation.
Maybe it's best to lay low and wait for all of this to blow over.
Proof that zombies can't pilot helicopters.
The favorite location of your teammate.
Being brave doesn't mean you're not scared. It means you're scared as hell, and then you pick up the shotgun anyway.
A design that Bill remembers from back before his hair greyed.
An ancient artifact from a religion that worshipped Assyrian, Sumerian, and Babylonian gods.
A golden figure of the sea goat, said to be the God of Water and Creation.
Somehow it feels more important than just any mangled zombie hand.
A digital camera that's never far from Zarina.
An ancient coin purchased by the wealthy to prove their devotion.
Don't let it fool you, leaving is never that easy.
What's this guy doing in The Entity's realm?
The Z in her name seemed beyond the comprehension of many, and Zarina found that she was often Karina.
A ceremonial dagger used to slice the tongue from a blasphemer.
An ancient tablet that depicts the High Priestess of Babylon purifying the masses.
A zombie nearly bursting with bile. Reminiscent of the time Mom undercooked the thanksgiving turkey.
An ominous sign, dripping in blood...
The first trophy Zarina won for her documentary work.
She took the words as truth and, as much as it pained her, accepted the necessity of spilt blood.
She did not understand how her mentor could question the gods.
She lied to the Maiden Guard to protect the man who raised her.
She begged the gods for an answer, and it arrived as a whisper, angry and thirsting for blood.
She allowed the whisper to influence her, no matter how difficult it pained her.
The world was snafued, and he was in the middle of it.
He found other survivors, even though one of them was a loudmouthed blowhard.
He fought alongside the others, freeing a young man from a perilous situation.
He was a value to his squad and he knew how to keep them in line.
He was ready, able to act on instinct. A part of himself even missed this feeling.
Wear it with pride!
An unlucky crow, stripped to its bones in the Observer's tower.
